	   ANKARA, Turkey _ About 10,000 Turkish soldiers cross into
northern Iraq to attack Kurdish rebels, and the government said it
might send forces into Syria to eradicate guerrilla bases there,
news reports say. TURKEY-KURDISH REBELS. Has moved. By Selcan
Hacaoglu.
	   ZAGREB, Croatia _ Adorned in the Vatican's traditional yellow
and white, the centuries-old southern coastal town of Split is set
for Pope John Paul II to celebrate Sunday Mass on the last day of
his visit to Croatia. CROATIA-POPE. Has moved. By Snjezana Vukic.
AP Photos MAR101-108, ZAG101-102.
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil _ President Fernando Henrique Cardoso is
the overwhelming favorite to win another four-year term on Sunday,
when Brazilians also choose 27 governors, all 513 federal deputies,
a third of the 81-seat Senate and 1,045 state legislators.
BRAZIL-ELECTIONS. Has moved. Polls open at 1100 GMT, close at 2000
GMT, final results expected Monday. By Peter Muello.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _BRAZIL-CANDIDATES _ A glance at Brazil's leading presidential
candidates.
	   RIGA, Latvia _ Latvians appear to have narrowly approved their
parliament's controversial measures to ease citizenship
requirements for the country's hundreds of thousands of stateless
Russians in a referendum, according to early results.
LATVIA-ELECTION. Has moved. By Jim Heintz. AP Photos RIG101-105.
