<HEADLINE>
Doohan wins fifth straight circuit title
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDs: will be led by 0900GMT with additional details, quotes &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PHILLIP ISLAND, Australia (AP) _ Australian Michael Doohan
captured his fifth consecutive world 500 c.c. motorcycle
championship when he rode his Honda to victory in Sunday's
Australian Grand Prix.
	   Doohan has an unbeatable points lead with just the Argentine
Grand Prix remaining in this year's championship.
	   Second on Sunday was New Zealander Simon Crafar on a Yamaha
followed by Spaniard Alex Criville and Brazil's Alex Barros, both
on Hondas. (djp)
