<SLUG> BC-China-Bus Crash </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eleven die in bus plunge off south China road
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ A bus packed with holiday travelers has veered
off a bridge in south China, killing 11 people and injuring 30, the
state-run Beijing Evening News reported Sunday.
	   Only one person, a small child, on the bus escaped injury when
it plunged about 80 meters (yards) in Hunan province's Cili county
on Thursday, the newspaper said.
	   Among those injured, some were in critical condition, it said.
	   The bus was one of three in a convoy taking travelers from
Wuhan, provincial capital of Hubei, to Zhangjiajie city in Hunan
for the four-day National Day weekend, which started Thursday.
	   The Beijing Evening News said the buses had been traveling all
night when the accident occurred early in the morning.
