<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Thai police arrest Malawi man with 21 kilograms of heroin
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ Police have seized 21 kilograms (46.2
pounds) of heroin from a man from Malawi as he was preparing to
board a flight to Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, Thai newspapers reported
Sunday.
	   Police quoted the man, identified as Yenri Suen Onabanjo, 32,
who was arrested Saturday, as saying was trying to smuggle the
drug, the Bangkok Post reported. It said the heroin had been
concealed inside audio loudspeakers.
	   Customs Department inspector general Somjainuek Engtrakul was
quoted as saying the suspect was part of a Nigerian-run
drug-smuggling ring.
	   The Customs Department has confiscated 80 kilograms (176 pounds)
of heroin in the past three months, the newspaper reported. Its
estimated cost in Thailand would be about 25 million baht (dlrs
633,000), but it would sell abroad for many times that value. 	   
