candidates.
	   RIGA, Latvia _ Latvians appear to have narrowly approved their
parliament's controversial measures to ease citizenship
requirements for the country's hundreds of thousands of stateless
Russians in a referendum, according to early results.
LATVIA-ELECTION. Has moved. By Jim Heintz. AP Photos RIG101-105.
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Prime Minister John Howard's conservative
government narrowly wins re-election and the chance to reform the
nation's tax system, but at the cost of a greatly diminished
majority in Parliament. AUSTRALIA-ELECTION. Has moved. By Peter
James Spielmann.
	   BAKU, Azerbaijan _ Authoritarian President Geidar Aliyev looks
set to win re-election in this oil-rich nation, but critics say
he's stacked the ballot in his favor and has not delivered on
promises to create prosperity. AZERBAIJAN-ELECTION. Has moved. By
Anna Dolgov.
	   NEW DELHI, India _ India's villagers may watch video e-mails in
local post offices, but outside the special booths, thousands of
children still die each year from preventable diseases.
