<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Oceania Nations Cup, 1st Ld Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
New Zealand upsets Australia in final
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDs: changes goal scorer in first graf, adds other details &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   BRISBANE, Australia (AP) _ Mark Burton scored in the 24th minute
Sunday to give New Zealand an upset 1-0 win over Australia in the
final of the Oceania Nations Cup soccer tournament at Suncorp
Stadium.
	   The win gives New Zealand a spot in January's Confederations Cup
tournament in Mexico City. Last December, Brazil beat Australia 6-0
in the Confederations Cup final at Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.
	   New Zealand's winner came after striker Vaughan Coveny beat two
diving tackles from Socceroo skipper Alex Tobin and Kasey Wehrman.
	   Coveny darted around a poor diving tackle by Tobin before laying
off for midfielder Burton who also beat a sliding tackle from
Wehrman before slotting home.
	   Australia's defeat was its first loss to New Zealand in nine
previous clashes since the Kiwis downed Australia 2-0 in a World
Cup qualifier in Auckland in 1989.
	   Burton's goal also was the first time Australia had conceded a
goal to New Zealand in eight matches.
	   Earlier, Fiji survived a late comeback attempt by Tahiti to win
4-2 to finish in third place in the six-team tournament that also
involved the Cook Islands and Vanuata.
	   (djp) 	   
</TEXT>
