	   ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) _ The price of shares in Switzerland's
telephone company Swisscom has been set at 340 Swiss francs (dlrs
250) each, the company said Sunday.
	   The issue was three-times oversubscribed, Swisscom said in a
statement. Overall demand amounted to around 65 million shares, it
added.
	   The 22,065 million shares, around 30 percent of the company's
share capital, will raise around 7.5 billion francs (dlrs 5.5
