<HEADLINE>
Murai wins Kosaido Ladies
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ICHIHARA, Japan (AP) _ Mayumi Murai birdied the final four holes
en route to a 1-under-par 71 Sunday that gave her a
come-from-behind victory by one stroke in the 60 million yen (dlrs
441,000) Kosaido Ladies.
	   Murai, an overnight co-leader, made some errors and plunged
three shots off the pace midway through with three bogeys.
	   On the back nine Murai regained the touch as she kept the
fairway, hit the ball close and sank the four straight birdies,
surging past Taiwan's Huang Yu-chen, veteran Nayoko Yoshikawa and
South Korean Ku Ok-hee, the other overnight co-leader.
	   The victory, at 3-under 213, was Murai's first in two years and
seventh overall. She took home the winner's prize of 10.8 million
yen (dlrs 80,000).
	   Huang shot a 69 for 214 and Yoshikawa a 71 to share third at 215
with Ku, who turned in a 73.
