<SLUG> BC-Spain-Drugs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spanish authorities seize 500 kilos of cocaine from French boat
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CADIZ, Spain (AP) _ Customs authorities intercepted a French
boat carrying 500 kilos (1,100 pounds) of cocaine near the southern
Spanish coast and arrested the two-person French crew, a spokesman
said Sunday.
	   Coast guards found the cocaine hidden in a false bottom of the
16-meter (yard) boat named Crisclo, a spokesman for the customs'
authorities in this southern Spanish city said on condition of
anonymity.
	   The Crisclo was taken to the nearby port of Barbate, the
spokesman said.
	   He refused to identify the detained Frenchmen who were placed
under police custody in Cadiz and can be held for up to 72 hours
before being charged or released.
	   No further information was available on the interception that
took place early Saturday in the Strait of Gibraltar _ a narrow
stretch of the Mediterranean that separates North Africa from
Europe.
	   (jt)
</TEXT>
