<SLUG> BC-Croatia-Pope, 3rd Ld </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDs: UPDATES with remarks on Kosovo, picks up 2nd graf
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Pope seeks to heal wounds of war
 &UR; With AP Photos
 &UR; By VICTOR L. SIMPSON &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   SPLIT, Croatia (AP) _ On a sun-basked seaside packed with
pilgrims, Pope John Paul II sought Sunday to heal the wounds left
by war and totalitarian rule and expressed ``anxious concern'' over
events in nearby Kosovo, the latest conflict brewing in the
Balkans.
	   ``May understanding, mutual respect, forgiveness and
reconciliation at last take the place of violence and
destruction,'' said the pope.
	   He called on the international community to provide ``timely
help,'' but did not mention the threat of airstrikes by NATO unless
Yugoslavia halts its assault on ethnic Albanians in Kosovo.
	   Hundreds of, 2nd graf
</TEXT>
