<SLUG> BC-Germany-Oktoberfest </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Attendance up, beer consumption down at this year's Oktoberfest
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MUNICH, Germany (AP) _ More visitors drank less beer at this
year's Oktoberfest, Munich's world-famous beer festival that ended
Sunday.
	   About 6.5 million people visited the 16-day annual event, 1.5
percent more than in 1997, said Munich tourist office chief Gabi
Weishaeupl.
	   Yet beer consumption dropped to its lowest level in years _ down
4 percent to 5 million liters (10.6 million pints). Weishaeupl
attributed the conflicting trends to more families coming to the
festival with their children.
	   Less beer consumed meant by the Bavarian Red Cross had less to
do. It said the number of intoxicated people it took care of
dropped from 345 in 1997 to 276 this year.
	   And police reported the number of people stealing beer steins
was down 15 percent.
 &UR; (pfg)	   
</TEXT>
