<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Refugees </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkish police intercept 500 would-be refugees
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CANAKKALE, Turkey (AP) _ Police detained 500 illegal immigrants
in the Dardanelles strait region early Sunday as they attempted to
board a ship headed for Italy, news reports said.
	   In the largest operation this year, police detained a group of
Syrians, Afghanis, Iraqi Kurds and Palestinians, including an
unspecified number of women and children, the Anatolia news agency
reported.
	   Officials could not be reached for comment.
	   Thousands of foreigners have been rounded up since the beginning
of the year after European nations put pressure on Turkey to impose
stricter control on its coasts and borders to prevent an exodus of
Kurds and other foreigners to Europe.
	   (ht-fd)
