----
KOSOVO: WRAP - APTN is hoping to have pictures from the 
village of Sebovac.  The body of an ethnic Albanian has been found
buried amongst the rubble of bombed houses. Will be wrapped with
pictures of Russia's defence minister meeting Milosevic in Belgrade
and comments from  British Defense Secretary George Robertson.
(First Run expected 1500 Europe Late)
----
POPE: WRAP - Hundreds of thousands of Roman Catholic pilgrims
flocked to the centuries-old southern coastal town of Split to see
Pope John Paul II celebrate Mass on the last day of his visit to
Croatia. Earlier his convoy traveled through the streets of the
town to cheering and applause. APTN will wrap Sunday afternoon's
mass with earlier coverage. (First Run Expected 1500 Europe Late)
----
CHECHNYA: KIDNAP - APTN is chasing the story of more Britons
kidnapped in Chechnya.  Unknown gunmen took four men hostage on
Saturday after a shoot out with
their bodyguards. The men were in Chechnya to install a cellular
phone system. (First run Expected 1500 Europe Late)
----
BRAZIL: VOTING - Brazilians go to the polls on Sunday.  APTN will
have pictures of early voting in Rio.  The country's 106
million voters are likely to reward President Fernando Henrique
Cardoso with a second term. His main challenger is the left wing
Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva.  (Expected F-L-A-S-H around 1330)
----
MALAYSIA - ANWAR - Thousands of women held a demonstration outside
the presidential palace in the Malaysian capital of Kuala Lumpa on
Sunday against Prime Minister Mahathir Mohammed.  The
demonstration came as former deputy prime minister Anwar Ibrahim was
sent back to prison after a hospital checkup.  He has accused police
of beating him while in custody. APTN also expects to have an
interview with Anwar's wife.  (First Run expected 1440 APTN
Eurovision)
----
BELGIUM: MARCH - Thousands of Belgians are expected to gather in the
capital of Brussels on Sunday in a march protesting ill
treatment of asylum seekers. The march comes just a week after the
funeral of a young Nigerian woman, seeking refuge in Belgium, who
died when police tried to subdue her with a pillow. (First Run
expected 1440 APTN Eurovision)
----
MIDEAST: WRAP -  Palestinian and Israeli negotiators are holding a
new round of talks in Jerusalem, aimed at ironing out outstanding
problems with interim peace deals.
US Secretary of State Madeleine Albright arrives in the region on
Tuesday. Also on Sunday new clashes have broken out in the West Bank
town of Hebron. APTN will be wrapping the stories and any further
developments. (First Run expected 1500 Europe Late)
----
US: IMF - Finance ministers and some central bankers from the
world's largest economies are holding talks in Washington, in a bid
to find a solution to the global economic crisis.  APTN will
have the latest. (First Run expected 1500 Europe Late)
----
RUNNING:  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
