<SLUG> BC-Sports-Track-Great Northern Run </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Thugwane, O'Sullivan win Great Northern Run half marathon
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEWCASTLE, England (AP) _ Olympic marathon champion Josiah
Thugwane of South Africa and former 5,000-meter world champion
Sonia O'Sullivan of Ireland won Sunday's wind-blown Great Northern
Run half-marathon.
	   Thugwane, fighting heavy winds off the northeast English coast,
finished the 13.1-mile (21.1-kilometer) race in 62 minutes 32
seconds, ahead of John Mutai of Kenya (62:50) and Martin Fiz of
Spain (63:30). Fellow Spaniard Ivan Sanchez was fourth (63:31).
	   On the women's side, O'Sullivan won in 71:50 followed by
Portugal's Manuela Machado (72:55) and Pamela Chepchumba of Kenya
(74:42).
	   (scw) 	   
