<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Mallorca Open </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kuerten beats Moya to win Mallorca tennis open
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: To be updated with doubles final result &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PALMA DE MALLORCA, Balearic Islands (AP) _ Brazil's Gustavo
Kuerten won the dlrs 475,000 Mallorca Open tennis tournament
Sunday, beating the favorite Carlos Moya of Spain in three sets.
	   World No. 5 Moya took the first set 7-6, before losing the next
two sets to the Brazilian 6-2, 6-3.
	   The two hours and four minute match disappointed the crowd
packed into the local bullfighting ring on this Mediterranean
island for whom Moya is a local hero.
	   The Kuerten-Moya final was billed as duel between two Roland
Garros champions, the Brazilian from 1997 and the Spaniard this
year's winner.
	   In the tournament's doubles finals, Pablo Albano and Daniel
Orsanic of Argentina was due to face Jiri Novak and David Riki of
the Czech Republic.
	   (jt)
</TEXT>
