<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italian Roundup, 1st Add </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ROME: next Saturday.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   At Florence, Rui Costa provided the pass and Edmundo the strike
at the end of a swift counterattack in the game's dying seconds.
The difference between this Fiorentina and that of recent years is
that Batistuta now gets consistent support from his teammates, both
in attack and on defense.
	   Fifth-place Udinese (2-1-1) nearly pulled off the upset, though,
when midfielder Jonathan Bachini's shot in the 52nd minute hit the
base of the post with Fiorentina 'keeper Francesco Toldo out of
position.
 &UR; Inter 2, Perugia 0 &QC; 
	   At Milan, Djorkaeff was brilliant, providing the playmaking and
leadership that some thought Inter would lack with the veteran
Baggio and Brazil's Ronaldo sidelined by knee injuries. Djorkaeff,
whose goal late in second-half injury time Wednesday gave Inter a
1-0 Champions League win over Austria's Sturm Graz, was quick to
get his head on the rebound after Perugia 'keeper Marco Roccati
failed to hold winger Francesco Moriero's 30-meter (yard) blast.
	   Inter also produced its top defensive effort of the season,
caging in dangerous Japanese midfielder Hidetoshi Nakata (three
goals in four games). Perugia fell to 0-2-2.
 &UR; Milan 2, Venezia 0 &QC; 
	   At Venice, Brazil's Leonardo provided the corner kick for
Bierhoff's early goal and then sent a 7-meter (yard) shot into the
low corner to seal victory in the 67th minute. Milan is 3-0-1,
while Venezia is 0-1-3 and the only club in the 18-team league
without a goal.
 &UR; Juventus 1, Piacenza 0 &QC; 
	   At Turin, Inzaghi headed in Alessandro Del Piero's free kick in
the eighth minute and Juventus (3-0-1) won despite the absences of
several starters. Piacenza is 1-1-2.
 &UR; Lazio 2, Cagliari 0 &QC; 
	   At Rome, Portuguese defender Fernando Cuoto scored from 2 meters
(yards) out in first-half injury time and, after Cagliari (1-1-2)
saw Uruguayan midfielder Fabian O'Neill expelled, Yugoslavian Dejan
Stankovic fixed the final score off Marcelo Salas' assist in the
69th. Lazio improved to 1-3-0.
 &UR; Bologna 0, Parma 0 &QC; 
	   At Bologna, the hosts (0-2-2) had Brazilian midfielder Eriberto
sent off with 28 minutes left, but Parma (1-3-0) could not
capitalize.
 &UR; Salernitana 1, Empoli 1 &QC; 
	   At Salerno, Roberto Breda's rising blast gave Salernitana
(0-1-3) the lead after 10 minutes, but Empoli (0-2-2) equalized in
the 33rd on defender Giorgio Lucenti's goal.
 &UR; Vicenza 1, Bari 0 &QC; 
	   At Vicenza, Uruguayan striker Marcelo Otero's header in the 16th
minute, the first goal Bari (1-2-1) has allowed this season,
decided the match. Vicenza is 1-1-2.
	   (hjf)
</TEXT>
