<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1094 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Weak high pressure north of the region in combination with a
tropical wave south of the islands will produce moderate to strong
east to northeast winds across the islands.
	   These winds will be more noticeable over the coastal waters,
producing very rough seas. A small craft advisory will continue in
effect for the coastal waters.
	   Skies will continue to be partly cloudy across most of the
region this afternoon, except for the west and southwest sections
of Puerto Rico, where an increase in cloudiness and showers is
expected.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 20 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 85 to 90. Wind
northeast 15 to 25 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms. Low 75 to 85. Wind northeast 5 to 15 mph.
	   Monday... Partly sunny, hazy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 15 to 20
mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 30 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High from around 75 in
the mountains, 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind northeast 15 to
25 mph.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers
or thunderstorms, becoming partly cloudy late in the evening.
Breezy in higher elevations. Low from near inland to around 80 on
the coasts. Wind northeast 10 to 20 mph.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy, hazy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms, mainly in the morning. High from around
75 on mountain peaks, 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind northeast
15 to 20 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 30 percent chance
of showers, mainly in the west. Slight chance of a thunderstorm.
High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. Breezy in higher elevations. A 30
percent chance of showers or thunderstorms. Low 70 to 80. Wind east
to northeast 10 to 20 mph.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy, hazy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. High 80 to 90. Wind east to northeast 15
to 20 mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Variably cloudy and breezy. A 40 percent
chance of showers or thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to
25 mph with higher gusts northwest and southwest coasts.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy in the evening with a 30 percent
chance of showers or thunderstorms, becoming partly cloudy by
midnight. Low 65 to 75. Wind northeast 5 to 15 mph.
	   Monday... Partly sunny and hazy in the morning, becoming breezy
with increasing afternoon cloudiness. A 40 percent chance of
showers or thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind northeast 15 to 25
mph.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 30 percent chance
of showers or thunderstorms, mainly in the west. High from 70 to 75
in the mountains, 85 to 90 in lower elevations. Wind northeast 15
to 25 mph with higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 40 percent chance of
showers and thunderstorms. Low 65 to 75. Wind northeast 10 to 20
mph.
	   Monday... Partly sunny, hazy and breezy in the morning.
Increasing afternoon cloudiness with a 40 percent chance of showers
and thunderstorms. High from 70 to 75 in the mountains, 85 to 90 in
lower elevations. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   This afternoon... Partly cloudy and breezy. A 30 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind
northeast 15 to 25 mph with higher gusts.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Isolated thunderstorms. Low 75 to 85. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph
and gusty.
	   Monday... Partly cloudy, hazy and breezy with a 30 percent
chance of showers. Chance for thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind
northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind east to northeast around 20 kt. Seas 6 to
7 ft. Scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 6 to 8 ft.
Scattered showers and isolated thunderstorms in bands and squalls.
	   Monday... Wind northeast near 20 kt. Seas 6 to 8 ft. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind east 20 to 25 kt. Near shore seas 6 to 7
ft. Offshore seas 8 to 10 ft. Scattered showers and isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to northeast at 15 to 25 kt. Near shore
seas 6 to 7 ft. Offshore seas 8 to 10 ft. Scattered showers and
thunderstorms in bands and squalls.
	   Monday... Wind becoming northeast near 20 kt. Near shore seas 5
ft. Offshore seas 6 to 8 ft. Widely scattered showers and isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   Small craft advisory in effect in outer waters.
	   This afternoon... Wind variable, mainly east 15 to 25 kt. Near
shore seas 2 to 3 ft. Outer waters seas to 5 ft. Widely scattered
showers and isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east to northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated evening thunderstorms.
	   Monday... Wind variable east to northeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2 to
4 ft. Widely scattered afternoon showers and isolated
thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Monday night through Thursday... Wind northeast 15 to 25 kt,
with seas 5 to 8 ft through Monday night. Wind and seas then
dependent on the future of a strong tropical wave currently across
the central tropical Atlantic.
	   This tropical wave and an associated low pressure system are
forecast to approach the northeast Caribbean from the east Tuesday
through Wednesday. They have the potential to intensify into a
tropical cyclone.
