<HEADLINE>
AEK beats Paniliakos, retains lead
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Paris Zoumboulis scored two goals as AEK
Athens beat Paniliakos of Pyrgos 3-1 at home Sunday, to retain the
lead in the Greek first division soccer league.
	   After six rounds, AEK has 16 points. It is followed by
Olympiakos Piraeus and Ionikos Nikea with 13 points each.
	   Olympiakos trounced Proodeftiki of Koridalos 6-1.
	   Ionikos hammered Ethnikos Piraeus 5-0 on two goals each by
Brazilian striker Paulo Andrioli in the 18th and 62nd minutes and
by Giorgos Stamboulis in the 18th and 64th. Scottish striker
Craig-James Brewster opened the scoring in the 10th minute.
	   AEK took an early lead with Zoumboulis in the 5th and came close
to a second three minutes later but Harris Kopitsis' shot went just
wide.
	   In the 23rd, it was Paniliakos' turn to miss a scoring
opportunity when goalie Chrisostomos Michailidis made a spectacular
save to a shot by George Papandreou.
	   Seconds before the end of the first half, Zoumboulis made it 2-0
off a center from Michalis Kasapis.
	   The visitors regrouped at half-time and drew within one goal in
the 74th when Vangelis Toyias beat Michailidis off a pass from
Yiannis Tatsis.
	   Paniliakos became more aggressive after the goal, launching one
attack after the other in an effort to level. But it was AEK which
scored again with a shot from the edge of the box by Toni Sawevski
in the 89th.
	   Olympiakos easily beat Proodeftiki 6-1 at home with three of its
players scoring two goals each.
	   The victory came four days after the Piraeus club defeated
Croatia Zagreb 2-0 in a game for the Champions League.
	   Olympiakos dominated the game particularly in the second half
when it netted four goals in eight minutes.
	   Alecos Alexandris scored in the 14th and 50th, Serbian striker
Ilija Ivic in the 25th and 52nd and Stelios Yiannacopoulos in the
48th and 56th minutes.
	   Albanian striker Rolanda Zaimi scored Proodeftiki's goal 32nd
minute.
