<HEADLINE>
US fighter makes emergency landing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ A US F-18 fighter carried out a successful
emergency landing at a NATO base on the island of Crete Sunday,
local media said.
	   The F-18 took off from the USS Eisenhower, the nuclear-powered
aircraft carrier currently in the Aegean Sea.
	   The plane landed at Souda air base when the pilot reported a
problem in the landing system, private Antenna radio said.
	   The aircraft carrier is taking part in NATO military exercises
and could be used in possible alliance air strikes to try and end
the Kosovo crisis.
