<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-France-Deadly Game </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Young couple to go on trial for grotesque killing
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By NICOLAS MARMIE &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ A young man and young woman go on trial Monday for
the murder of a friend who prosecutors contend was killed during a
perverse love scene, its fatal ending written in advance.
	   The defendants, identified as Veronique Herbert, 20, and
Sebastien, 19, are to be tried behind closed doors at the court for
minors in Bobigny, outside Paris, because of their age at the time
of the March 1996 crime.
	   They both risk life in prison for the death of Abdeladim, then
16. Prosecutors claim he was killed while making love to Veronique,
allegedly stabbed to death by her and Sebastien.
	   The deadly drama stirred controversy at the time, with experts
focusing on the effects of violence in movies. According to the
prosecution, Veronique had a morbid fascination for films,
especially Oliver Stone's 1994 movie ``Natural Born Killers.''
	   The film follows a young, much-in-love couple on a killing
spree, with the attendant media attention.
	   According to the prosecution, Veronique, described by
psychiatrists as a ``calm, serious, good student'' from
Gournay-sur-Marne, outside Paris, had told friends she and
Sebastian planned to commit a murder. Plastic sacks and a metal saw
were bought in advance.
	   On the night of March 2, 1996, the pair allegedly lured
Abdeladim to Sebastian's family home, saying Veronique was
attracted to him. The young girl and Abdeladim become intimate.
	   Sebastien allegedly refuses Abdeladim's demands to leave the
room. According to the prosecution, Sebastien takes two knives from
a drawer and allegedly stabs the young man in the neck, after
asking the woman's permission.
	   Then, in what the prosecution's dossier likens to a ``horror
film,'' the young woman allegedly orders Sebastien to ``finish him
off,'' while she allegedly plunges the second knife into the
victim's stomach.
	   The pair, in a panic, bury the victim outside the house, wash
off and flee in the car of Sebastien's father.
	   Police found the couple, who confessed to the crime, in the
Cantal region of central France three days later.
	   (eg-parf)
</TEXT>
