<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Italy Roster </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Zoff names Ventola, Totti for Euro 2000 qualifier
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ROME (AP) _ Looking for fresh firepower, Italy coach Dino Zoff
on Sunday called up young strikers Nicola Ventola and Francesco
Totti for next weekend's Euro 2000 qualifier against Switzerland.
	   Zoff also selected two relatively untested goalkeepers,
20-year-old Gianluigi Buffon and Francesco Toldo, in naming his
20-man roster for the Group 1 match Saturday at Udine. Regular
starter Angelo Peruzzi is hurt.
	   With Christian Vieri and Roberto Baggio, Italy's top two
forwards at last summer's World Cup, nursing injuries, Zoff turned
to two of the most promising players in the country.
	   Ventola, 20, leads Internazionale of Milan with three goals in
Serie A play, while Totti, 22, is the focal point of AS Roma's
potent attack.
	   Lazio of Rome defender Giuseppe Favalli is the only other
newcomer.
	   Just one player was called from outside the Italian League,
defender Christian Panucci of Spain's Real Madrid.
	   Italy beat Wales 2-0 Sept. 5 in Zoff's debut as coach. He
replaced Cesare Maldini after the Azzurri were bounced from the
World Cup in the quarterfinals.
	   The roster:
	   Goalkeepers _ Gianluigi Buffon (Parma), Francesco Toldo
(Fiorentina)
	   Defenders _ Fabio Cannavaro (Parma), Giuseppe Favalli (Lazio),
Paolo Maldini (Milan), Christian Panucci (Real Madrid), Gianluca
Pessotto (Juventus), Moreno Torricelli (Fiorentina)
	   Midfielders _ Demetrio Albertini (Milan), Jonathan Bachini
(Udinese), Giuliano Giannichedda (Udinese), Dino Baggio (Parma),
Diego Fuser (Parma), Luigi Di Biagio (Roma), Eusebio Di Francesco
(Roma)
	   Forwards _ Enrico Chiesa (Parma), Alessandro Del Piero
(Juventus), Filippo Inzaghi (Juventus), Francesco Totti (Roma),
Nicola Ventola (Inter).
	   (hjf)
</TEXT>
