<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Netherlands-Roundup,0246 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Confused Ajax loses again; Feyenoord drops first points
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ The top Dutch teams had a tough
day Sunday as Ajax went down 2-0 at lowly Sparta and Feyenoord
scraped a point with a 1-1 tie at FC Twente.
	   Feyenoord (6-1-0), eliminated this week from the UEFA Cup,
remains unbeaten and leads the league with 19 points, two over
Twente and Vitesse Arnhem, with a game in hand.
	   Ajax's second defeat of the season reduced it to sixth, with 14
points, and the third of the traditional Dutch ``big three'', PSV
Eindhoven, is in 10th place with just 10 points.
	   Sparta strikers Erik Tammer and Dennis Krijgsman did the damage
with a goal each, exposing the frailty of Ajax defenders Ole
Tobiasen and Mario Melchiot respectively.
	   Feyenoord was stunned by Jan Vennegoor of Hesselink's header at
62 minutes. Peter van Vossen made it worse just two minutes later
when he was sent off for a wild tackle from behind on German
defender Joerg Sobiech.
	   But it took just five minutes more for Twente's Erik ten Hag to
produce a bizarre back-headed own goal and pull the Rotterdammers
back into the game.
	   In Sunday afternoon's other games: Vitesse Arnhem played a
scoreless draw with De Graafschap Doetinchem, NEC Nijmegen won 3-2
at FC Utrecht and AZ Alkmaar downed RKC Waalwijk 3-2.
	   And in the evening game, SC Heerenveen climbed to fourth with a
2-1 victory over NAC Breda.
</TEXT>
