<SLUG> BC-France-Aga Khan </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Aga Khan fetes May marriage
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CHANTILLY, France (AP) _ King Juan Carlos of Spain was among 800
weekend guests feting the May marriage of Prince Karim Aga Khan,
the spiritual leaders of the world's Ismaili Muslims.
	   The Aga Khan wed Gabriele zu Leiningen in a private ceremony at
his estate, Aiglemont, in Gouvieux, 25 miles north of Paris near
Chantilly, on May 30. It was the second marriage for both.
	   The October reception was planned at the time of the marriage.
	   The Spanish monarch and his wife Sophie, along with former
French President Valery Giscard d'Estaing, were among the guests
invited to the reception.
	   Juan Carlos returned to Spain by special plane Sunday afternoon,
according to police in the town of Oise.
	   The Frankfurt-born bride, 35, a consultant at the U.N.
Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization in Paris, took
the Muslim name ``Inaara'' upon her marriage to the 61-year-old Aga
Khan, his office said at the time, adding that the princess'
six-year-old daughter from her first marriage to Karl-Emich Prince
zu Leiningen was to live with her mother in France and Switzerland.
	   The Aga Khan is the 49th imam of the Ismaili community which has
a following of 12-15 million people worldwide. He has three
children from his first marriage to English-born Princess Salimah,
all of whom work at his headquarters at Aiglemont.
	   (eg-var-parf)
</TEXT>
