<SLUG> BC-Greece-Highway Robbery </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Armed men rob Ukrainian tourists on bus, escape police dragnet
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Two unidentified gunmen on Sunday held up
a bus with 25 Ukrainian tourists aboard, robbed them of their money
and jewelry, and escaped with a third accomplice on a waiting
scooter.
	   According to police, the 25 were traveling to the Ukranian
capital of Kiev aboard the bus along with the two men. Police did
not know their nationality.
	   Authorities said the bus left central Athens in the early
evening headed for the northern border with Bulgaria. Just 23
kilometers (14 miles) from the capital, the two men pulled out
pistols, ordered the driver to stop the bus and robbed the
passengers of an estimated dlrs 10,000 and an unknown quantity of
jewelry.
	   An accomplice was waiting for them on a scooter. Police launched
a manhunt, but were unable to locate the three men on the scooter.
	   Although armed robberies are not rare in Greece, it was the
first reported theft of its kind in recent memory.
	    &UR; pq
</TEXT>
