<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Spanish Roundup </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
League leader Real Madrid loses 1-0 to struggling Betis
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By JOHANNA TUCKMAN &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   MADRID, Spain (AP) _ Real Madrid lost its grip of the Spanish
soccer league Sunday, losing 1-0 at home to last placed Betis in
the fifth round.
	   Nigerian international Finidi George's 55th minute smash past
sprawled German keeper Bodo Illgner was enough to give Betis its
first league victory this season.
	   Not that the victory was easy, with Madrid keeping up the
pressure throughout a frantic second half.
	   Coming out keen after the break, Madrid's Clarence Seerdorf of
Holland hit the post within the first minute before Finidi's goal
hit from well outside the box temporarily threw the European
Champions off balance.
	   But Betis failed to capitalize, missing several chances to
extend its lead and giving Madrid time to pull its attack together.
	   Among the clearest opportunities to equalize was a shot from
Raul Gonzalez knocked over the bar by Betis keeper Antonio Prats,
and a thundering shot at goal from Brazilian Roberto Carlos.
	   But the equalizer did not come, and powerhouse Real Madrid
stayed on 10 points, two points behind the new leader of the first
division Zaragoza.
	   Earlier Sunday, Zaragoza gathered up its 12 point total with a
2-0 victory over modest Extremadura.
	   After a goalless first half, Argentina's Kily Gonzalez put
Zaragoza one up in the 56th minute.
	   Bosnian Savo Milosovic scored the second and final goal five
minutes before the final whistle, redeeming himself after fluffing
a penalty conversion five minutes after the break.
	   In Saturday's only fifth round game FC Barcelona trounced
Valencia 3-1, notching up a total of nine points, still one behind
archrival Madrid and three behind the leader.
	   In Sunday's other games, Oviedo claimed a place in the top half
of the table, trouncing Atletico de Madrid 3-1 with two goals from
midfielder Ivan Iglesias and a third from Panamanian Julio Cesar
Dely Valdez.
	   Only a doubtful penalty call allowed the visiting team to
partially redress the balance.
	   Iglesias' first goal came in the 32nd minute and his second in
the 70th, while Dely Valdez added the third in the 84th. Back from
injury, Brazil's tireless midfielder Juninho successfully hit home
a penalty to make it 3-1 just before the match ended.
	   Celta, meanwhile, convincingly beat Athletic de Bilbao 3-2 in a
mid-table battle.
	   Argentine Fernando Caceres headed Celta one up in the 16th
minute and Luboslav Penev of Bulgaria scored the visiting side's
second goal in the 31st.
	   Julen Guerrero got one back for Athletic de Bilbao 10 minutes
after the break, but Penev successfully hit home a penalty to make
it 3-1 in the 62nd.
	   Ismael Urzaiz scored a second compensation goal for Athletic
just before the final whistle blew.
	   In other fifth round matches Sunday, Mallorca drew 1-1 with
Tenerife as did Espanyol against Villarreal, Real Sociedad defeated
Deportivo de La Coruna 2-0, Salamanca beat Valladolid 1-0, and
Racing de Santander overcome Alaves by the same score
 &UR; Mallorca to Tenerife &QC; 
	   Mallorca went ahead in the 12th minute with a goal from
Brazilian Andre Luiz Moreira. Argentine Leo Biagini scored the
equalizer in the 50th minute.
 &UR; Espanyol 1, Villarreal 1 &QC; 
	   Espanyol drew 1-1 with visiting first division newcomer
Villarreal after a goalless first half.
	   The fist goal was scored for Espanyol by Quique Martin Sanchez
in the 55th minute, with Antonio Diaz scoring the equalizer in the
77th.
 &UR; Real Sociedad 2, Deportivo La Coruna 0 &QC; 
	   Oscar de Paula scored for Real Sociedad with 42 minutes played,
and Francisco Jose de Pedro added a second for the home side with a
penalty conversion in the 60th.
 &UR; Salamanca 1, Valladolid 0 &QC; 
	   Argentine Martin Alejandro Cardetti scored the only goal of the
match just before the break that was enough to give Salamanca a 1-0
victory over Valladolid.
 &UR; Alaves 0, Racing de Santander 1 &QC; .
	   Pedro Munitis scored the only goal of the match in the 15th
minute to give Racing de Santander a 1-0 victory over division
newcomer Alaves.
	   (jt)
</TEXT>
