<SLUG> BC-France-Britain-Kosovo </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
With Britain-Kosovo
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; French foreign minister meets British counterpart on Kosovo &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine was meeting
Sunday night with his British counterpart to discuss the situation
in Kosovo where threats of a NATO strike loom, the Foreign Ministry
said.
	   A ministry spokesman, speaking on customary condition of
anonymity, provided no details on the meeting between Vedrine and
Robin Cook.
	   The encounter was preceded by a lengthy telephone conversation
between Vedrine and U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, the
spokesman said.
	   Tension surrounding an eventual NATO strike was mounting as
Western leaders sought a way to force Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic to halt attacks on ethnic Albanians and seek a political
settlement to the Kosovo problem.
	   Britain has said it will send four more ground-attack aircraft
to a NATO base in southern Italy on Monday, doubling the number of
Royal Air Force planes there in readiness for an attack on Kosovo.
	   British Defense Secretary George Robertson said in a British
Broadcasting Corp. television interview Sunday that ``a whole
series of options have been worked through and that we are ready to
move on them.''
	   France is not a member of NATO's military wing, but is
nevertheless consulted.
	   (eg-var-parf)
</TEXT>
