<SLUG> BC-Sports-Track-Lidingoloppet,0166 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chemobo wins world's largest cross country race
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; RETRANSMITS to fix slug; new for some lines &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   LIDINGO, Sweden (AP) _ Defending champion Isaac Chemobo bested
the course record by a whopping one minute and 41 seconds Sunday as
he won the men's 30-kilometer race in Lidingoloppet, the world's
biggest cross-country festival.
	   Chemobo's winning time was 1 hour, 33 minutes and 33 seconds.
Fellow Kenyan William Musyoki set the old course record in 1996.
	   Philip Rugut and Wilson Omwoyo made it a podium sweep for Kenya,
finishing in 1:34.27 and 1:36.59 respectively. Portugal's Joao
Lopes placed fourth in 1:37.23.
	   Former world marathon champion Douglas Wakiihuri of Kenya was
11th.
	   Finland's Annemarie Sandell, who finished fifth in the recent
World Half Marathon Championships, won the women's 15K for the
fourth time in 53.52.
	   More than 23,000 runners competed in the two-day festival on
Lidingo Island outside Stockholm.
</TEXT>
