<SLUG> BC-Canada-Hospital Demolished,0167 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Major hospital complex in Alberta demolished after closure order
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photo &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   CALGARY, Alberta (AP) _ A seven-building complex that used to be
Calgary's leading hospital was blasted into rubble by demolition
experts Sunday, just a few months after it was closed to save
money.
	   While thousands of residents watched from their homes and from
hillside parks, Calgary General Hospital tumbled down in a span of
about nine seconds after the first charge of dynamite exploded.
	   A thick cloud of dust and smoke enveloped nearby homes, many of
which had been evacuated in advance of the demolition.
	   Dozens of hospitals across Canada have been ordered closed in
the past few years as provincial governments try to trim spending
on health care. But Calgary General was the first major hospital in
the country to be demolished.
	   It was of three hospitals in Calgary to be closed recently. The
city of 800,000 is now left with only one trauma center.
</TEXT>
