	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _BRAZIL-CARDOSO _ Cardoso's past inspires confidence in
Brazilians.
	   ANKARA, Turkey _ With reports of Turkish troops massed on
Syria's border, President Suleyman Demirel warns that Turkey won't
let its neighbor continue sheltering Kurdish rebels. TURKEY-KURDISH
REBELS. Has moved. By Harmonie Toros. AP Photos ANK101-102.
	   HEBRON, West Bank _ New clashes break out in advance of a Jewish
holiday and the Palestinian lands remain sealed off, with Israel
and the Palestinians each saying it is up to the other whether any
accord can be reached on an Israeli troop pullback.
ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT. AP Photo JRL104.
	   ROME _ Italy's Communists vote to withdraw support for Premier
Romano Prodi's coalition, a move that could trigger the collapse of
one of the country's longest-lived postwar governments.
ITALY-POLITICS. Has moved. By Frances D'Emilio.
	   ULAN BATOR, Mongolia _ Police place a leading democratic
politician under guard following the slaying of a popular
government minister . MONGOLIA-POLITICIAN KILLED. Has moved. By
Michael Kohn.
	   SAN CRISTOBAL DE LAS CASAS, Mexico _ Ignoring pleas from
authorities and the Roman Catholic Church to turn out for elections
in troubled Chiapas state, voters opt to stay away in droves.
MEXICO-CHIAPAS ELECTIONS. RECAP expected by 0300 GMT; first results
expected by early Monday. By Trina Kleist. AP Photos SCC101-104.
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Prime Minister John Howard says he will try
to push his tax reforms through Parliament as quickly as possible
after he scraped back into power on the weekend, despite pledges
Monday from senators to thwart him. AUSTRALIA-ELECTION. Expected by
0400 GMT. By Peter James Spielmann. AP Photo SYD101.
	   RIGA, Latvia _ With the divisive and distracting issue of
liberalized citizenship for ethnic Russians put behind them,
Latvian politicians turn to the question of forming a government.
LATVIA-ELECTION. Has moved. By Jim Heintz.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ANALYSIS-LATVIA-LEARNING TO FORGET _ Liberalizing laws for
Russians shows Latvia is at a turning point.
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands _ Families of victims killed in the 1992
crash of an Israeli cargo plane tearfully mark the sixth
anniversary amid new revelations that the jet was carrying an
ingredient for nerve gas. NETHERLANDS-CRASH MEMORIAL. Has moved. By
Jenifer Chao. AP Photo AMS101.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Joint Congressional Economic Committee holds
hearing on IMF reform in Washington on Tuesday. Winners of
``alternative Nobels'' are announced Wednesday in Stockholm,
Sweden.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   MANDELA CAMP, Sudan _ Two million Sudanese living in camps
ringing the capital, Khartoum, are among 4 million displaced people
in Africa's largest country, the most in the world. FEA-SUDAN-A
TOLERABLE TRAGEDY. To move as wire time permits. By Anthony Shadid.
AP Photos NY304-NY306.
	   CEUTA, Spain _ The Strait of Gibraltar is a treacherous place.
Still, it remains a busy threshold for impoverished Africans who
are looking for a better life in Europe. FEA-SPAIN-EUROPEAN
THRESHOLD. To move as wire time permits. By Kernan Turner. AP
Photos NY307-NY310. AP Graphic GIBRALTAR.
	   YOUR QUERIES: The Associated Press World Service editors in
charge are Kim Gamel and Charles Gans. Suggestions and story
requests to The Associated Press World Service are welcome. Contact
your local AP bureau or the AP International Desk in New York,
telephone (1) 212-621-1650, fax (1) 212-621-5449.
